args: Now then, where could those fiends be?
Er, Orsem? I'm happy to have your help,\nbut are you sure this is a good idea?
Well, you're not a fighter, are you?
I'd think that battling monsters and so on\nmight be dangerous for a person with\nyour...specific skill set.
Don't you worry yourself about that!\nAnd hey, isn't it the same for you,\n{player_name}?
Yeah! I mean, you're a prince, right?\nIsn't it dangerous for you to be out\nslaying fiends and whatnot?
Well, I suppose it is dangerous,\nbut it's also my duty.
I'd do anything to protect my land and\npeople. They're very important to me.
And is that cause one you would give up\nyour dreams for?
Found you at last. Have at you, fiends!
Orsem, wait! You can't just charge at\nthem skates-first!
Think you can catch me, villains?!\nHa ha ha! Come at me!
Oh wow... He's skating around the fiends\nso much that it's confusing them!
Too bad for you! I'm over here, fiends!
What the...? He jumped and landed on the\nfrozen fiend's back!
A perfect landing! ...Whoa!\nYou can still move, eh?!
Phew! Thanks for the assist there,\n{player_name}!
You can't ever let your guard down during\na fight, Orsem.
Even so, I'm pretty surprised by how well\nyou did out there.
I want to prove that someone can fight\neven when they're still into skating.
What exactly do you mean by that?
You remember how I told you that skating\nwas very popular where I come from?
Note that I said ＂was.＂\n...Meaning ＂used to be.＂
But every year, the number of fiends in my\nhomeland kept growing, and my friends\nsoon abandoned their skates for the sword.
Even though they all supposedly loved it,\nthey gave it up.
Why do you have to stop skating?!\nI thought you loved it!
What about our dream of us spreading its\njoy all around the world?!
We can't just mess around with inane\ndreams forever, Orsem.
Maybe you ought to quit being\nirresponsible and face reality.
Just like you, my home is precious to me,\nand I would do anything to protect it.
Still, I could never give up skating!
Why must I choose between the two things\nthat are important to me?!
I'm not sure what to say, Orsem...
Anyway, that's why I trained to develop a\nskating fighting style—so I could battle\nfiends and continue my love of the blades.
It seemed a good way to take care of\nboth problems at once.
Also, it's when times are hardest that it's\nMOST important to keep dreaming.
Do you think it's bad to dream,\n{player_name}?\n
Not at all. I've got a dream of my own,\nin fact.
I want to create a kingdom where everyone\ncan live happily.
That's why I understand how you feel.
So let's work as hard as possible and\nmake our dreams come true no matter\nwhat hardship comes our way.
